<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-23T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-23T22:00:00-05:00" n="128" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">548.G1/46: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Consul General at Hamilton</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Beck</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-23T23:00:00-04:00">April 23,
                                1943—11 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>92. Your 128, April 22, 7 p.m. For Dodds from Long. We assume that
                        transportation costs on Rumanian vessels for refugees in question proceeding
                        to Palestine will be in the neighborhood of $100,000 to $150,000. Please
                        advise. We have arranged to have funds available <pb facs="0174" n="164" xml:id="pg_164"/> and are glad to be able to state that the American
                        Government will share transportation costs with the British Government.
                        Because of the nationality of the vessels involved we prefer to make payment
                        to British Government. [Long.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>